==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eroded
<hw>E*rod"ed</hw>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Eaten away;
gnawed; irregular, as if eaten or worn away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the edge worn away so as to
be jagged or irregularly toothed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erodent</ent>⟦br⟧
